The National Pension Commission (PenCom) has approved the withdrawal of over N1.20 trillion from Retirement Savings Accounts (RSAs) from inception of the Contributory Pension Scheme (CPS) to September 30, 2020. This was disclosed in reports recently released by PenCom. Retirees on programmed withdrawal top the list of withdrawals from Retirement Savings Accounts (RSAs) with a total withdrawal of N693.87 billion, followed by Death Benefits N215.28 billion, 25% Withdrawal N137.45 billion, Retirees on Annuity N125.49 billion and Enbloc withdrawal N29.78 billion as well as Retirees on Programmed Withdrawal. The total number of retirees currently receiving their pensions under the Programmed Withdrawal agreements with Pension Fund Administrators (PFAs) is 258,800 (Federal Government 55.84%, State Governments 8.87% and private sector 35.29%). The sum of N682.86 billion has been paid to retirees as lump sum while N11.01 billion has been paid as monthly-programmed withdrawals from inception to 30 September 2020. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCEÂ DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! On Annuity, retirees who have chosen to receive their pension via annuity provided by Life Insurance companies grew to 81,925 with Federal Government 59.66per cent, State Governments 12.39per cent and private sector 27.95per cent while the sum of N120.98 billion has been paid as lump sum, N4.51 billion has been paid as monthly annuity pension payments to retirees on annuity plan, the report stated. In a similar arrangement Retirees Enbloc Withdrawal grew to N29.78billion. CIIN Groans Over Dearth Of Professionals In Specialised Areas BREAKING: NAICOM Complies With Court Order To Suspend Recapitalisation These are retirees whose Retirement Savings Account (RSA) balances were N550,000 or below and considered insufficient to procure a Programmed Withdrawal or Annuity of a reasonable amount over an expected life span, and the retirees were subsequently paid the total balance in their RSAs. The sum of N29.78 billion has been paid to 120,046 (Federal Government 5.53%, State Govt 3.50% and private sector 90.97%).